\newlabel{sub@fig:iv_surface}{{b}{7}{\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
\newlabel{fig:term_residuals}{{2c}{7}{\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
\newlabel{sub@fig:term_residuals}{{c}{7}{\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
\newlabel{fig:iv_heatmap}{{2d}{7}{\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
\newlabel{sub@fig:iv_heatmap}{{d}{7}{\relax }{figure.caption.7}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Multi-expiration term structure calibration (NVDA, 2 to 46 DTE). \textbf  {(a)}~ATM implied volatility as a function of days to expiration. Market ATM IV (blue markers) exhibited a U-shaped term structure; the fitted model (red curve) captured the trough near DTE~$\approx 8$ (32.5\% IV) and the rise to 41\% at 46~DTE using the quadratic extension $\beta _5 (\ln \tau )^2$. \textbf  {(b)}~IV smile curves at each of six expirations (2, 4, 7, 14, 25, 46~DTE). Market observations (markers) and model predictions (lines) are colored by DTE; 0~DTE data (diamonds) were excluded from the fit due to gamma compression. The skew flattened with increasing maturity, consistent with $\beta _3 > 0$. \textbf  {(c)}~IV residuals (model $-$ market) by moneyness, colored by DTE. Most residuals fell within $\pm 2$\% IV, with no systematic bias across the moneyness range. \textbf  {(d)}~Model-predicted IV surface as a function of moneyness and DTE (log-scaled). White contour lines mark 35\%, 45\%, and 55\% IV levels; white circles indicate market observations used for calibration. The overall RMSE was 1.15\% IV.}}{7}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:term_structure}{{2}{7}{Multi-expiration term structure calibration (NVDA, 2 to 46 DTE). \textbf {(a)}~ATM implied volatility as a function of days to expiration. Market ATM IV (blue markers) exhibited a U-shaped term structure; the fitted model (red curve) captured the trough near DTE~$\approx 8$ (32.5\% IV) and the rise to 41\% at 46~DTE using the quadratic extension $\beta _5 (\ln \tau )^2$. \textbf {(b)}~IV smile curves at each of six expirations (2, 4, 7, 14, 25, 46~DTE). Market observations (markers) and model predictions (lines) are colored by DTE; 0~DTE data (diamonds) were excluded from the fit due to gamma compression. The skew flattened with increasing maturity, consistent with $\beta _3 > 0$. \textbf {(c)}~IV residuals (model $-$ market) by moneyness, colored by DTE. Most residuals fell within $\pm 2$\% IV, with no systematic bias across the moneyness range. \textbf {(d)}~Model-predicted IV surface as a function of moneyness and DTE (log-scaled). White contour lines mark 35\%, 45\%, and 55\% IV levels; white circles indicate market observations used for calibration. The overall RMSE was 1.15\% IV}{figure.caption.7}{}}
